		<div class="post-229 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-denmark category-festivals category-film category-sita-sings-the-blues" id="post-229">


<div class="post-headline">		<h2>			
			<a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/2008/03/29/copenhagen-so-far/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to Copenhagen so far">Copenhagen so far</a></h2>
		</div>

<div class="post-bodycopy clearfix"><p>A quick update from abroad: This NATFILM festival is sweeeet. Copenhagen is possibly the most beautiful city I&#8217;ve ever visited &#8211; sorry other cities, but the medieval architecture here wins my heart. I just saw Guy Maddin&#8217;s fantastic new film &#8220;My Winnipeg,&#8221; which I missed in Berlin. Guy Maddin is one of the few filmmakers I can honestly call inspiring. Unfortunately he couldn&#8217;t attend NATFILM in person. But I did get to meet John Sayles and his partner Maggie and a bunch of really nice Danish film people at a superb homecooked dinner in a palatial (literally, in a palace) apartment here. Sweet, I tells ya.</p>
<p>&#8220;Sita&#8221; screens at 3pm tomorrow at Empire Bio.
<p>Continue reading <a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/2008/03/29/copenhagen-so-far/">Copenhagen so far</a></p>
